@@TJvItemsPanel
<TITLEIMG TJvItemsPanel>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.PanelsBevelsAndGroups.Panels
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Displays a list of "buttons" where each button is a string in a string list.
Description
  TJvItemsPanel is a simple class that can divide its client area into buttons where each button
  receives a caption as determined by the Items property. If Items contains 6 strings, TJvItemsPanel
  displays 6 buttons, if Items contains 2 strings, TJvItemsPanel displays 2 buttons etc.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.AutoGrow
Summary
  Specifies whether the controls size is adjusted to show all buttons.
Description
  Set AutoGrow to true to make the control resize to show all buttons. When AutoGrow is set to true,
  the following happens:

  * AutoSize is set to false.
  * Align is set to alNone.
  * The Height or Width (depending on the value of Orientation) is set to ItemHeight * Items.Count.
See Also
  Height, Width

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.AutoSize
Summary
  Specifies how buttons are sized.
Description
  Use AutoSize to specify how buttons are sized when the control is sized. If AutoSize is true, buttons
  are sized so all buttons can be seen in the control. If AutoSize is false, buttons are sized
  according to the ItemHeight property. If AutoSize is set to true, AutoGrow is set to false.
See Also
  TJvItemsPanel.AutoGrow, TJvItemsPanel.ItemHeight

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.Clickable
Summary
  Specifies if buttons can be clicked or not.
Description
  Use Clickable to specify if clicking on a button is allowed or not. If Clickable is true, items
  behave as buttons and the OnItemClick event is triggered.
See Also
  TJvItemsPanel.OnItemClick

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.GetItemAt
Summary
  Returns the item at the specified position.
Description
  Call GetItemAt to obtain the index for the item found at the position specified by the X and Y
  parameters. X and Y specify the coordinates of the position, in pixels, relative to the top left
  corner of the control. If there is no item at the location, GetItemAt returns -1.
Parameters
  X - The X coordinate of the location.
  Y - The Y coordinate of the location.
Return value
  Returns the index of the item or -1 if no item was found at the specified location.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.GetItemRect
Summary
  Returns the coordinates for an item.
Description
  Call GetItemRect to retrieve a TRect for the item at the specified index.
Parameters
  Index - Index of the item in the list
Return value
  A TRect in client coordinates that describes the position and size of the specified item.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.HotTrack
Summary
  Specifies whether items are highlighted when the mouse passes over them.
Description
  Set HotTrack to True to provide visual feedback about which item is under the mouse; the color
  specified by HotTrackColor is used for the frame around the item. When HotTrack is False, there is no
  visual feedback when the mouse passes over the item.
See Also
  TJvItemsPanel.HotTrackColor

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.HotTrackColor
Summary
  Specifies the color of the frame around items when the mouse hovers over them.
Description
  Use HotTrackColor to specify a color to use for the frame around an item when the user hovers the
  mouse over it. HotTrackColor is used only if HotTrack is set to true.
See Also
  TJvItemsPanel.HotTrack

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.ItemHeight
Summary
  Specifies the size of items in the control.
Description
  Use ItemHeight to specify the size of items in the control. ItemHeight is not used if AutoSize is
  true.

  Depending on the value of Orientation, ItemHeight affects either the height (Orientation is
  opVertical) or the width (Orientation is opHorizontal) of the items.
See Also
  TJvItemsPanel.AutoGrow, TJvItemsPanel.AutoSize

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.Items
Summary
  Provides indexed access to the items on the control.
Description
  Use Items to access the items in the control using an index. Items is of type TStrings and you can
  use the methods of TStrings to Add, Remove and rearrange items.
See Also
  TStrings

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.OnItemClick
Summary
  Occur when an item is clicked and Clickable is set to true.
Description
  Write a handler for the OnItemClick event to take specific action when the user clicks an item in the
  control.
Parameters
  Sender    - The object that triggered the event.
  ItemIndex - The index of the item that was clicked.
See Also
  TJvItemsPanel.Clickable

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvItemsPanel.Orientation
Summary
  Specifies the display direction of the items.
Description
  Use Orientation to specify how the items in the control are displayed. If Orientation is
  poHorizontal, items are displayed from left to right and ItemHeight refers to the width of the items,
  if Orientation is poVertical, items are displayed from top to bottom and ItemHeight refers to the
  height of the items.
See Also
  TJvItemsPanel.ItemHeight

